##What do grassroots community investigators do every day

The function introduction, reconstructs our life with the narrative beauty.

I find it reassuring to see the sanitation workers in orange uniforms, the traffic police in green vests patrolling the streets, the passing yellow bikers, the 24 hour clerks at the drugstore.
And I'm one of them.

Work in China | series 35

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, I went downstairs to take out the trash. I saw my high school classmate, Lili, with a mortar and bucket hanging in her arms and a roll of paper under her arm, pasting "citizen Suchi" on the unit door.
Lili, a single mother, has worked in the community of this small northern city for nearly 10 years. Usually I work busy, and her contact is not much, thought they work will be very easy, is after dinner and uncle aunt chat on the line. This Spring Festival has been staying at home, only to see her busy all day, and her on Wechat chat off and on for several days, only to know that her work is much more complicated than I thought.
On Weekdays, during the renovation of an old residential area, she will coordinate with the construction bureau, the Social Enterprise Bureau and the planning and Real Estate Bureau to take part in the demolition of illegal buildings; when doing the work of letters and visits, she will have to go through each item, cooperate collectively, and take responsibility to the people; when the three cities unite to create, she will strengthen publicity, fulfill the responsibility, do a good job seed prohibition, Drug Prohibition, re-employment support to do not miss a member, to provide care, love, sincere assistance. In addition, like with the police to investigate the whereabouts of suspects, service for special groups, take care of their basic life, and even to help residents to clean up the sewers... Everything, everything will come.
To catch up with the current special situation, the work has added several new items: not only responsible for household survey-related matters, but also at any time to answer the residents of the advisory phone calls.
The article was dictated by Lily.

New Year's Eve at noon, sitting for more than 3 hours bus, I finally took my son back home, ready to spend a reunion with their parents. Did not think, delicious food just to the table, the mobile phone screen on the pop-up leader in the work group notice: "All staff please January 25 back to work, no special reason not to leave. "
I was like a frost-hit Eggplant, 7-year-old son saw, timidly asked me: "Mom, you want to go back to work overtime? " Son from birth is a person with me, growing up, my work often have unexpected events, the numerous sudden turns made him extremely sensitive.
Just last October, the city began a three-city joint venture (to create a national civilized city, create a national health city, create a national food safety demonstration city) , and all of our community workers are on hand, take Part in demolishing illegal buildings on weekends. Just in time for his son's birthday, Ben promised to take him to have western food first, then to the Children's Paradise, and finally bought a dancing robot as a birthday gift. But on that day, I can only send my son to the custody class.
After work at around 8 pm, I went to the bakery and bought the last cake the size of my fist. When I went to the foster care class, my son was alone in the classroom. I snuck in the back door and stood behind him, while my son was drawing pictures of me and him on his birthday. In the middle is a giant cake, my son and I and a robot sitting around the cake, wish together. I was very sad, gently holding him in his arms, and then took out the bag just bought the cake, the son this tears for the smile: "Mom, I thought you forgot to pick me up! " That cold night, I was full of guilt, i feel like I'm always missing out on his growth.
This time is the same, I still can only hold him in his arms, and explained the situation to the parents, the parents let me rest assured that the son they help take care of first. At 5 p.m. , it was getting dark, and I was on the bus for the return trip. There weren't many people on the bus, only three or five wearing masks. On the way, I received a task from my leaders ———————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————————— --. As soon as I got back into the city after 8 p.m. , I ran down the street to the pharmacy, thinking I'd buy some face masks and alcohol.
On New Year's Eve, the pharmacy would be closed by now, and tonight it would be packed. "Masks are sold out" signs are posted on the doors of nearly all pharmacies, and clerks who walk into pharmacies to ask about masks peddle their stock of Banlangen root and hand sanitizer.
Originally planned to return home for the New Year, the family basically did not reserve food. I rushed to the nearest supermarket, close to the store, there are fewer people than the sales staff, eggs, vegetables are sold out. I had to carry two packets of instant noodles, add some ham sausage preserved vegetable, is my New Year's Eve dinner.
Back home, cooked noodles, swallowed a few mouthfuls, the heart is badly blocked.

Since "three cities create" , our community has done "a hundred families, know a hundred feelings, understand a hundred difficult, warm hundred hearts" of the household survey work.
Including the poor people in the community, the elderly living alone, disabled families, the unemployed, we must do a good job in helping. Distribute promotional materials, explain the support programs, and listen to their feedback, as far as possible for everyone to solve practical difficulties.
We once heard that the son of an old man from a Shidu family was killed in the line of duty. He himself is disabled, and living with his grandson is hard. The old man told me that the difficulties in life could be overcome after a fashion, but he really didn't know what to do because the child's Hukou was not in the locality and could not be enrolled in school. Finally, the community came forward and school district to communicate, the school accepted the children free of charge.
But this investigation of the epidemic, and even more different from the past, this is related to the health and safety of every resident, the task has become more difficult.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, I arrived at work at 6:30 to begin "simulation training" so that I could officially enter the house at 8:30 with the alcohol, gloves and mask I had prepared.
The requirements for this household survey are extremely strict, requiring detailed understanding of the subject's physical condition, so as to achieve "clear return route (clear) , return to the place of origin, clear means of transport, clear physical condition, clear prevention and treatment measures, clear contact personnel. ". In addition, this household inquiry, "need to maintain a safe distance, but also need to deal with some emergencies. ".
In order to carry out the work smoothly, the director asked us to do a good job in preparation before entering the house, to formulate a detailed work programme and survey plan, to collate the entry forms, to estimate the number of households to visit each day and the route to visit, and to allocate the survey time reasonably, "The time is too short to understand the situation, and too long will lead to resentment. " At the same time, and in advance to communicate with the relevant departments to assist in the work, the police first called Xiao Wang, but also had to contact the neighborhood committee, the head of the owners' Committee, and the property management well, "understand the basic situation, try to cooperate, reduce household resistance, every day survey no less than 150 households. ".
Our survey time is also based on the principle of convenience to the residents, set at 9:30 am to 11:30 am, 2:00 pm to 4:30 pm, if the household is empty during the survey period, need to visit again at 7:00 pm to 8:30 pm. Because the personnel is nervous, can only "single combat" . Before setting out, the office reminded us again: "residents to stand farther before opening the door. "
However, there was trouble on the first day of work.
In contrast to the active cooperation of some elderly residents, some residents because of panic, clearly heard someone walking around the house, but no answer how to knock on the door, I can only wait until tonight.
In the morning, the property clerk told me that a resident of the 5th floor, which had been vacant for three days, had returned with a White Mazda and Wuhan License Plate, "At first it was parked in the community parking lot, but last night it was moved to the south side of a small secluded garden, and the license plate was covered with a disc. "
I listened to, in the mind is startled, immediately make a phone call and the leadership reflect, contacted piece police Xiao Wang again. According to the information provided by the property, we went to the door, heard a noise in the room, but knocked on the door a few times, but no one always pay attention.
During the leadership training, it was repeatedly stressed that even in times of emergency, we should be polite, patient and good-natured. We must first identify ourselves. I opened my mouth outside the door, "Hello residents, I am a community staff, you need to take a little time for the registration of mobile staff, for the sake of everyone's health and safety, please cooperate! "
Still no answer.
Xiao Wang knocked on the door, took out the police officer card aimed at the Mirror: "I am the police, please open the door, please cooperate! "
After about 10 minutes, the door opened slightly. A man in his 60s showed half his face, all alert and guarded, and asked in a southern accent, "what's the matter? "
"Uncle, some residents reported that your home is back from Wuhan, now the virus has spread seriously, we need to know your specific itinerary. "
When GRANDPA heard this, he suddenly got angry and said, "what do you care? This is a private matter. It's none of your business. "
"Your personal information will be kept confidential... "
"How can you keep a secret? I just walked in the door and someone called the police on me. What did I do? "
"special period, please cooperate with our work, this is also responsible for yourself. " Police Xiao Wang immediately said.
"How can you be responsible for me? Lock me up and put me in isolation? What's the big deal with the police? No one in my family is sick! If you don't leave, I'll sue you for disturbing the people. Get Out! "
Just as the old man was about to close the door, Xiao Wang quickly put his foot under the crack of the door. "We are doing this for everyone's safety... "
Unable to close the door, he took out his mobile phone and began to videotape us. "You want to scare me? I'm going to post something on the Internet and see how you treat us! "
"The network news also needs the content to be true, you this kind of news belongs to spreads the rumor, can cause the bad social influence, must punish legally! " Xiao Wang Zheng color way.
After a while, the elder brother calmed down and said, "what do you want to ask me? I'm not ill. "
I quickly opened the registration form: "Do you have a fever at home? "
"No, I'm the only one at home. I'm perfectly healthy. "
Wang and I could see at least four sets of dishes still on the table, and we could hear the children's voices as if they were suddenly covered with their hands.
"Sir, you can't make a false report, " I patiently advised him.
"I'M NOT LYING! "
At this moment, the door of the House on the left suddenly opened, and an aunt with a mask stuck her head out, pointing at his home, he said, "the old couple returned home with their son, daughter-in-law and grandson. Last night his son went to the community hospital with a fever just after 10 o'clock. I heard them say they were going to drive to Shenyang this evening. If they do catch the plague, they don't know how many people will be hurt. "
The neighbor on the right also opened a small vent on the door and said, "I heard someone coughing at night. The children were up in the middle of the night and seemed to be sick. "
"If you're sick, you have to go to the hospital, " I said quickly. "Besides, there are children at home. You have to think of your children as well as your adults. Zhong Nanshan has said that truth is as important as real medicine. "
In everyone's joint efforts to persuade, GRANDPA and his family finally willing to go to the hospital for examination. Fortunately, that afternoon the results of the clinical examination came out, although there is a fever at home, the child is also coughing, but are common cold. In addition, we also learned that although their car is hanging Wuhan License Plate, but in fact on weekdays are doing cooked food business in Shenyang, has not returned to Wuhan for five or six years.
This time to small town, was intended to spend the New Year with in-laws, did not think of all the way because of a license plate, by a lot of obstacles, only to put the pent-up emotions vent to us.

Every employee in the community pays attention to the public number of the government in order to watch the real-time report of the epidemic and get an accurate picture of the situation at the first time. After three days of 'zero diagnosis' in the town, my heart began to settle and I continued to brace myself for the possibility that -- with a small city and a relatively small floating population -- I might be able to survive.
But my lucky streak was soon broken. On January 28, the news that "4 cases of imported COVID-19 pneumonia in our city have been diagnosed" was flashed on my friends' circles. One of them belongs to our community.
That morning, we received reports that people returning from Wuhan in the community were suspected to have been infected. A look at the detailed address, is the area I am responsible for, can only "resigned" to do the investigation. The property led me to the door. I took a deep breath, covered up my face mask, knocked on the door, and was soon answered. I quickly reported myself to the door, and said, "don't open the door, I just ask you. "
I asked him some questions through the door, and the young man was also very cooperative. He said that he had been working in Wuhan and arrived in Huanggang on January 22. On the night of January 23, he took the D740 train to Beijing. On the morning of January 24, he arrived at Beijing West Station, then by subway to Beijing south, the same day by high-speed rail back to the city, when the body is not any discomfort, they took a taxi home. Only yesterday I felt a little uncomfortable and went to the hospital to have a check-up.
I reported his condition immediately, and soon after, the young man was taken into quarantine and subsequently diagnosed. I thought I was one of those close contacts who should be quarantined, but since we hadn't even met, I was excluded.
Unfortunately, that night I started to have a fever, and the next day my throat was too swollen to speak, and I had a cough and a stomachache. I tried to make a phone call to my parents and son, said some words of encouragement, but tears burst into my eyes, and always felt like I was in the care of Gu. From the other side of the phone came the young son's voice: "Mom, when are you coming to pick me up? I have a cold again, and miss you! "
The baby started crying on the phone, and I started crying on the phone. Then with a thermometer, temperature 38 degrees 5, rushed to call the leadership leave. The director thought I was being quarantined at home because of contact with a diagnostician, and immediately said, "you can rule it out. No one's here. It's fine. "
When I told her about my condition, her voice rose an octave at once. "really sick? This is the moment of truth, the hour of employment, we are the first line of Defense in front of the common people, if you are afraid to die, if you deceive your superiors, know the consequences, feel free to quarantine yourself at home, if you have any problems, just call Wang!"
I didn't have time to call Xiao Wang, xiao Wang's wechat message came first: "sister, I heard you are sick? Sister, we are comrades in arms. Although there are unpredictable dangers in the work, but we work so hard, good luck will surely favor us. "
Xiao Wang and I have known each other for more than three years. At first he was like a child, with dimples in his face and a blush when he spoke. However, the work has no implication, we have been a tacit understanding, is a good partner.
On second thought, he was consoling himself by saying so. A 28-year-old boy, when the mission with his mother embroidered amulet, transport fever patients should be an ambulance work, but the hospital is busy, coupled with many fever patients do not cooperate, refused to go to the hospital. Xiao Wang, a local police officer, has taken six fever patients to the hospital in a police car. He disinfects the car with alcohol every time he returns, and then disinfects himself.
This Spring Festival, he did not dare to go home from the lunar twenty-eight, has been living in the institute.
"sister, I think you will be fine, you must not worry, take medicine for two days. There is no medicine at home, I will send it to you. Anyway, we are both in the same boat, if you catch it, I will not run away. " Xiao Wang is still cheering me up.

Lying in bed, I feel dizzy, even a cup of boiling water people do not have, can only force the body to find water to drink, and then give his son years ago to take a little cold medicine.
At 8 pm, my father, who usually only answers the phone with his mobile phone, suddenly sent me a message on Wechat: "Send me a photo. "
How can we take a picture of him at this point? I had to send him old photos from my phone. After more than an hour, the father's message came again: "I just miss you! "
Dad is a very conservative and serious person, if not really miss me, would not have said such a thing in his life. After all these years, I'm too much for them to worry about.
One year it snowed so hard that I had to rush back to the community to register as unemployed. My mother had to bring me a bag of home-made food, so that my father took me to the station by electric bike, only to be halfway there because the snow was too heavy to drive the electric car. Dad did not let me get off to walk, just pushed the electric car to send me to the station, that way is mostly uphill, looking at Dad's back, I think only in the hearts of my parents, I will never grow up the child.
But now, not only have I failed, I have a son to raise, and I can't fall into Harvard -- I think of it, and my defenses are up.
Remember the first few days of the investigation, every day will take off their own clothes and shoes to the door, the home with alcohol to wipe disinfection, serious hand washing several times, and then carefully take a bath. Later thought, anyway, I am a person, tired out of time, this set of procedures on the Save, home wash hands, head to sleep, is it really because of his slack?
After crying for a while, I thought, I have no physical contact with the infected person, I can't scare myself. Add to this season is the flu, work intensity, early to late, easy to catch cold, low immunity is also very likely. And even pneumonia doesn't mean viral pneumonia, common bacterial pneumonia means fever; even viral pneumonia doesn't mean a new crown, it could mean H1N1 and H1N1..
In this series of self-persuasion, I slowly fell asleep. After two days'rest at home, the fever has broken. Thank God, really just a common cold, my heart gradually light up.

On the ninth day of the New Year, I went back to work.
I am in charge of the area has nearly 2000 residents, pre-screening work has been basically completed. But in order to deal with the growing epidemic, the work also needs to be further refined, the workload has increased rapidly.
The leader's request is, every day in the morning and evening 2 times the inspection plot environment, carries on the clean-up disinfects, the key place daily disinfects not less than 2 times. The collection point of Rubbish Bin and waste protective articles in the community is the most important. Every day, the municipal garbage disposal center will send someone to collect and destroy the rubbish at regular time and place, but there will still be old scavengers to turn it over. We all need to supervise and manage.
In addition, registration of community rental housing personnel is also required. If an outbreak is not reported in a timely manner, the landlord must be held accountable; some families who handle "red affairs" or "White Affairs" must also file for management, the community should be responsible for guiding the residents to stop "Red Affairs" and "White Affairs" .
In addition to these "required actions, " my mobile phone, wechat also continued to receive "urgent orders" : During my illness, delivery boys kept calling me, telling me that some neighborhoods were too scared, and they blocked the gate of the neighborhood, they couldn't get into the neighborhood, customers do not receive food, constantly complain about them, I have to rush to the community to coordinate;
In my previous household survey, I added many wechat accounts of people returning from Hubei Province or passing through Hubei Province. They had to be quarantined at home for 14 days as required. Most of the old communities where they lived had no property, and I could only be found on wechat, say there's no food in the house, or send me a long grocery list, urging me to hurry up and get it there, or else I'll go out and buy it myself -- unless, of course, it's my job to handle it
Then there are the psychological issues -- people lock themselves in a confined space for so long that they are prone to anxiety, which is often met by self isolated outsiders chatting with me on Wechat to cope with.
There is a local from Henan to see her grandfather, originally planned to help her daughter to look after six months of grandchildren, the daughter also gave him a good rental house. Did Not expect him to take the train carriage Wuhan passengers, is also a "close contact with the crowd" , can only be isolated in the rental house first. I spoke to him almost every day on Wechat for at least 20 minutes at a time, speaking quickly and with a strong accent. The only thing I could fully understand was that before the end of each conversation, he will use "Hepu" to say to me: "little girl, every day and you talk, I feel much brighter. "
I was happy and sad to be recognized for my work. This time of year, I am taking my son out to visit relatives, set off firecrackers, play cards, a lively family. And now, I'm home alone, sick, and we're all alone.

On the first day back at work, I was so busy that when I got home at night, my back ached and I fell asleep. Unexpectedly, at 3:00 in the morning, I was awakened by a sudden ringing of the telephone.
Confused and picked up the phone, there a cry: "sister, you come to save me, my intestines fell out... " is the isolation of the second pregnant woman Xiaoling, to the due date of more than 1 month. As I comforted her, I put on my clothes and ran to her house.
Xiaoling's family returned from a trip to the provinces on January 22. During the preliminary investigation, they learned that everyone else in the family had fever except her. In this case, isolation is necessary to rule out the possibility of encountering a new coronavirus carrier on the journey. The community had to deal with it as a matter of urgency, separating the family, keeping the feverish under observation in the new house and Xiaoling in the old one. Her family's old house and my family is just before and after the building, Xiaoling's husband asked me to take care of her these days.
It was, eighteen degrees outside, and I called Wang as I ran, sounding like I was in shock -- An ambulance was on call 24 hours a day, never in time, i let Xiao Wang drive the police car to come, and then called Xiao Ling's husband to tell him the situation, there is also very anxious, but also in isolation period and can not go out, can only ask me everything.
She rushed up to the 5th floor. When she came in, she was lying on the Sofa in the living room. Her face was Pale and she bit her lip. Her Nails made the SOFA creak. I couldn't carry her on my own. Luckily, Wang arrived five minutes later.
We dressed Ling in a thick down jacket and put on a mask. Wang held her while I rushed downstairs with a delivery box. He drove the police car straight to the city's Maternity Hospital -- the only one without a fever clinic. He took her to the emergency room. I went to the emergency room and told the hospital that the pregnant woman was in self-imposed quarantine.
After examination, the doctor found that the umbilical cord prolapse, premature rupture of membranes, not a great threat to the mother, but the baby will be very dangerous —— because it will lead to the baby blocked blood flow, resulting in acute hypoxia. The doctor said, vaginal examination, B ultrasound examination is definitely too late to do, need immediate surgery, umbilical cord blood circulation block more than 7 minutes, the baby will not be saved.
Xiao Ling cried when Xiao Wang and I were frightened. Fortunately, the doctor listened with a stethoscope and said there was a faint fetal heart sounds. Then, doctors and nurses immediately put on protective equipment, informed the operating room open green channel, Xiao Wang ran before and after all kinds of procedures. But when it came time for the family to sign, neither Wang nor I were immediate family. Quickly Call Xiaoling's husband to explain the situation, he cried like a child on the other end of the phone: "If there is a problem must protect adults Ah! "
I didn't know until I hung up, but when I called outside to check on my registration, the surgeon told the nurse to print the woman's hand and begin the operation, Florida. Six minutes later, the baby was born. Although some mild asphyxia at first, but after the neonatal pediatrician's rescue, soon improved.
The doctors and nurses, including myself and Wong, cheered as if the baby were ours -- a precious commodity that made me miss my son even more.
Wang collapsed in a chair and said: "sister, this is to give me early 'induction training' ? I was scared to death. "
Only then did we realize that we had done nothing to protect ourselves. We didn't even know when we lost our masks.
The hospital had placed Suzu in isolation, and the attending doctors told me that they were also afraid, that if they did deliver a baby with a coronavirus infection, it would be very dangerous, as if they were only wearing protective masks, but dressed in normal scrubs, "we do not have protective clothing, all supplies are to support the first line. "
Fortunately for us, Ling was later tested negative at the hospital, and everyone was safe. Xiaoling's family has not passed the quarantine period, fortunately they contacted a distant relative, let her take care of Xiaoling Mother and son first.

After taking Ling to the hospital, my heart tensed even more, worried that if I did anything wrong, it would be a matter of life and death. In Times of crisis, it is necessary to coordinate the normal operation of businesses and medical service stations in your area, especially the lives of the elderly, pregnant women and special groups, so as to achieve a smooth transition.
We have already spoken to the Community Health Service, who can ensure that one person stays behind every day, making it easier for nearby residents to receive injections and medicines, and to avoid cross-infection on the way to hospital. Of course, when the elderly to go to the hospital to do dialysis or as Xiaoling special circumstances, we can only see a way out.
In addition, the community has a number of "voluntary support" business, there are some lost mood. The owner of a small restaurant has closed its doors, but there are some lonely old people nearby who still call for food —— -- There are two lonely old people in their 90s who can't even go downstairs, it's a lot of trouble.
The rent, water and electricity were to be paid, the prices of vegetables, grain and oil rose, but the boss's food prices remained unchanged. It's New Year's, and with the epidemic, the waiters don't want to come back to work. The boss can only one person live in the store, every day from buying to cooking to the elderly to send three meals, are their own hands-on.
"The neighbors all know that I'm holding out, people are afraid to go out, more and more people are calling for meals, but I can only take the lonely old man first, I'm tired to death every day, but the income is much less than usual, I can only trouble your street, see if you can find a way to help me, even if you can help me to find a temporary worker, at this point, people don't even come to work for three times the salary... "
That's what the boss said. I can't think of anything right now. That day, Henan sent me another wechat call -- as if he had been quarantined for 16 days, so there should be no problem. I quickly asked if I would like to come to the restaurant to help, I immediately agreed to carry the quilt directly to the store, and the boss a chat, two people also quite hit it off. That's a good thing, too.
And the focus of my work has shifted more to the lonely elderly in my community.
As it is in the Old City, the community households are mostly middle-aged and elderly people over 50 years old, there are 186 people aged 80-90 years and 7 people aged 90-99 years.
One of them, a 94-year-old grandmother named Chen, is semi-self-sufficient. In order to improve her quality of life, I have paired up with her. Visit her once a week, bring her monthly allowance on time, take her to the bath regularly, send her a mooncake from the street every New Year, it is part of my daily work.
After spending a lot of time with the elderly, I've found that treating the elderly like a child, and how you treat them will reciprocate thoughtfully. In retrospect, it may have been because I didn't spend much time around my parents, so I turned my attention to my parents and moved it to my grandparents in the community.
These days, young people's cell phones are flooded with information, but some old people do not watch the news and do not know the seriousness of the epidemic. When it comes to understanding, you can explain it a few times, but some old people are very stubborn. An aunt insisted on buying a brand of health care products, not to buy, they kept calling crying. In the end, I had to go to six pharmacies to get what she wanted.
In addition to this, in addition to regular "re-stocking" of food-deficient and food-deficient isolation personnel, you have to call them every day and tell them: "If you have a fever, you must report it immediately. You are responsible to everyone but yourself. " When does this end.

Occasionally, though, the frustration can be dispelled by more emotion.
One day, I went down to the mini-mart to buy instant noodles. "Girl, " said the supermarket GRANDPA, "eat this at night where there is nutrition? To increase immunity, not afraid of disease. " He said, he gave me cut a piece of his home-made sauce beef, wrapped with plastic bags stuffed to me.
Some community friends said on Wechat that 5 yuan a pack of disposable masks sold for 15 yuan a year ago. She asked someone to buy two packs and two N95s for me to keep, saying that I could not enter the front line without any protective measures.
And I think maybe it was the 10 years of effort, that was seen by the community, witnessed by them, recognized by them. Last year alone, I visited nearly 2,000 households, issued more than 300 certificates, registered 500 documents and visited 36 enterprises for the re-employment of the unemployed. I know, as long as the steadfast service for you, you can see, I can also worthy of heart.
Lily is doing a vehicle check-up
Now, my work has been gradually straightened out, and I haven't missed a single thing that I should have done during the non-epidemic period, such as going to the Labor Bureau every week to submit various reports, including assistance to families in difficulty, application forms for re-employment, and assistance to families who have lost their only child, for the key period of the fight against the epidemic, have also done a variety of exit and entry registration, vehicle inspection, etc. .

The work is small and tiring. But I guess it's called doing your job.
I find it reassuring to see the sanitation workers in orange uniforms, the traffic police in green vests patrolling the streets, the passing yellow bikers, the 24 hour clerks at the drugstore. And I'm one of them.
Like the blood of a stagnant life, we pool our meager resources to make the city work.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, I arrived at work at 6:30 to begin "simulation training" so that I could officially enter the house at 8:30 with the alcohol, gloves and mask I had prepared.
The requirements for this household survey are extremely strict, requiring detailed understanding of the subject's physical condition, so as to achieve "clear return route (clear) , return to the place of origin, clear means of transport, clear physical condition, clear prevention and treatment measures, clear contact personnel. ". In addition, this household inquiry, "need to maintain a safe distance, but also need to deal with some emergencies. ".
In order to carry out the work smoothly, the director asked us to do a good job in preparation before entering the house, to formulate a detailed work programme and survey plan, to collate the entry forms, to estimate the number of households to visit each day and the route to visit, and to allocate the survey time reasonably, "The time is too short to understand the situation, and too long will lead to resentment. " At the same time, and in advance to communicate with the relevant departments to assist in the work, the police first called Xiao Wang, but also had to contact the neighborhood committee, the head of the owners' Committee, and the property management well, "understand the basic situation, try to cooperate, reduce household resistance, every day survey no less than 150 households. ".
Our survey time is also based on the principle of convenience to the residents, set at 9:30 am to 11:30 am, 2:00 pm to 4:30 pm, if the household is empty during the survey period, need to visit again at 7:00 pm to 8:30 pm. Because the personnel is nervous, can only "single combat" . Before setting out, the office reminded us again: "residents to stand farther before opening the door. "
However, there was trouble on the first day of work.
In contrast to the active cooperation of some elderly residents, some residents because of panic, clearly heard someone walking around the house, but no answer how to knock on the door, I can only wait until tonight.
In the morning, the property clerk told me that a resident of the 5th floor, which had been vacant for three days, had returned with a White Mazda and Wuhan License Plate, "At first it was parked in the community parking lot, but last night it was moved to the south side of a small secluded garden, and the license plate was covered with a disc. "
I listened to, in the mind is startled, immediately make a phone call and the leadership reflect, contacted piece police Xiao Wang again. According to the information provided by the property, we went to the door, heard a noise in the room, but knocked on the door a few times, but no one always pay attention.
During the leadership training, it was repeatedly stressed that even in times of emergency, we should be polite, patient and good-natured. We must first identify ourselves. I opened my mouth outside the door, "Hello residents, I am a community staff, you need to take a little time for the registration of mobile staff, for the sake of everyone's health and safety, please cooperate! "
Still no answer.
Xiao Wang knocked on the door, took out the police officer card aimed at the Mirror: "I am the police, please open the door, please cooperate! "
After about 10 minutes, the door opened slightly. A man in his 60s showed half his face, all alert and guarded, and asked in a southern accent, "what's the matter? "
"Uncle, some residents reported that your home is back from Wuhan, now the virus has spread seriously, we need to know your specific itinerary. "
When GRANDPA heard this, he suddenly got angry and said, "what do you care? This is a private matter. It's none of your business. "
"Your personal information will be kept confidential... "
"How can you keep a secret? I just walked in the door and someone called the police on me. What did I do? "
"special period, please cooperate with our work, this is also responsible for yourself. " Police Xiao Wang immediately said.
"How can you be responsible for me? Lock me up and put me in isolation? What's the big deal with the police? No one in my family is sick! If you don't leave, I'll sue you for disturbing the people. Get Out! "
Just as the old man was about to close the door, Xiao Wang quickly put his foot under the crack of the door. "We are doing this for everyone's safety... "
Unable to close the door, he took out his mobile phone and began to videotape us. "You want to scare me? I'm going to post something on the Internet and see how you treat us! "
"The network news also needs the content to be true, you this kind of news belongs to spreads the rumor, can cause the bad social influence, must punish legally! " Xiao Wang Zheng color way.
After a while, the elder brother calmed down and said, "what do you want to ask me? I'm not ill. "
I quickly opened the registration form: "Do you have a fever at home? "
"No, I'm the only one at home. I'm perfectly healthy. "

"I'M NOT LYING! "

If they do catch the plague, they don't know how many people will be hurt. "

This Spring Festival, he did not dare to go home from the lunar twenty-eight, has been living in the institute.

"sister, I think you will be fine, you must not worry, take medicine for two days. There is no medicine at home, I will send it to you. Anyway, we are both in the same boat, if you catch it, I will not run away. " Xiao Wang is still cheering me up.

Lying in bed, I feel dizzy, even a cup of boiling water people do not have, can only force the body to find water to drink, and then give his son years ago to take a little cold medicine.
At 8 pm, my father, who usually only answers the phone with his mobile phone, suddenly sent me a message on Wechat: "Send me a photo. "
How can we take a picture of him at this point? I had to send him old photos from my phone. After more than an hour, the father's message came again: "I just miss you! "
Dad is a very conservative and serious person, if not really miss me, would not have said such a thing in his life. After all these years, I'm too much for them to worry about.
One year it snowed so hard that I had to rush back to the community to register as unemployed. My mother had to bring me a bag of home-made food, so that my father took me to the station by electric bike, only to be halfway there because the snow was too heavy to drive the electric car. Dad did not let me get off to walk, just pushed the electric car to send me to the station, that way is mostly uphill, looking at Dad's back, I think only in the hearts of my parents, I will never grow up the child.
But now, not only have I failed, I have a son to raise, and I can't fall into Harvard -- I think of it, and my defenses are up.
Remember the first few days of the investigation, every day will take off their own clothes and shoes to the door, the home with alcohol to wipe disinfection, serious hand washing several times, and then carefully take a bath. Later thought, anyway, I am a person, tired out of time, this set of procedures on the Save, home wash hands, head to sleep, is it really because of his slack?
After crying for a while, I thought, I have no physical contact with the infected person, I can't scare myself. Add to this season is the flu, work intensity, early to late, easy to catch cold, low immunity is also very likely. And even pneumonia doesn't mean viral pneumonia, common bacterial pneumonia means fever; even viral pneumonia doesn't mean a new crown, it could mean H1N1 and H1N1..
In this series of self-persuasion, I slowly fell asleep. After two days'rest at home, the fever has broken. Thank God, really just a common cold, my heart gradually light up.

Xiaoling's family returned from a trip to the provinces on January 22. During the preliminary investigation, they learned that everyone else in the family had fever except her. In this case, isolation is necessary to rule out the possibility of encountering a new coronavirus carrier on the journey. The community had to deal with it as a matter of urgency, separating the family, keeping the feverish under observation in the new house and Xiaoling in the old one. I didn't know until I hung up, but when I called outside to check on my registration, the surgeon told the nurse to print the woman's hand and begin the operation, Florida. Six minutes later, the baby was born. Although some mild asphyxia at first, but after the neonatal pediatrician's rescue, soon improved.

Wang collapsed in a chair and said: "sister, this is to give me early 'induction training' ? I was scared to death. "

"

After taking Ling to the hospital, my heart tensed even more, worried that if I did anything wrong, it would be a matter of life and death. In Times of crisis, it is necessary to coordinate the normal operation of businesses and medical service stations in your area, especially the lives of the elderly, pregnant women and special groups, so as to achieve a smooth transition.
We have already spoken to the Community Health Service, who can ensure that one person stays behind every day, making it easier for nearby residents to receive injections and medicines, and to avoid cross-infection on the way to hospital. Of course, when the elderly to go to the hospital to do dialysis or as Xiaoling special circumstances, we can only see a way out.
In addition, the community has a number of "voluntary support" business, there are some lost mood. The owner of a small restaurant has closed its doors, but there are some lonely old people nearby who still call for food —— -- There are two lonely old people in their 90s who can't even go downstairs, it's a lot of trouble.
The rent, water and electricity were to be paid, the prices of vegetables, grain and oil rose, but the boss's food prices remained unchanged. It's New Year's, and with the epidemic, the waiters don't want to come back to work. The boss can only one person live in the store, every day from buying to cooking to the elderly to send three meals, are their own hands-on.
"The neighbors all know that I'm holding out, people are afraid to go out, more and more people are calling for meals, but I can only take the lonely old man first, I'm tired to death every day, but the income is much less than usual, I can only trouble your street, see if you can find a way to help me, even if you can help me to find a temporary worker, at this point, people don't even come to work for three times the salary... "
That's what the boss said. I can't think of anything right now. That day, Henan sent me another wechat call -- as if he had been quarantined for 16 days, so there should be no problem. I quickly asked if I would like to come to the restaurant to help, I immediately agreed to carry the quilt directly to the store, and the boss a chat, two people also quite hit it off. That's a good thing, too.
And the focus of my work has shifted more to the lonely elderly in my community.
As it is in the Old City, the community households are mostly middle-aged and elderly people over 50 years old, there are 186 people aged 80-90 years and 7 people aged 90-99 years.
One of them, a 94-year-old grandmother named Chen, is semi-self-sufficient. In order to improve her quality of life, I have paired up with her. Visit her once a week, bring her monthly allowance on time, take her to the bath regularly, send her a mooncake from the street every New Year, it is part of my daily work.
After spending a lot of time with the elderly, I've found that treating the elderly like a child, and how you treat them will reciprocate thoughtfully. In retrospect, it may have been because I didn't spend much time around my parents, so I turned my attention to my parents and moved it to my grandparents in the community.
These days, young people's cell phones are flooded with information, but some old people do not watch the news and do not know the seriousness of the epidemic. When it comes to understanding, you can explain it a few times, but some old people are very stubborn. An aunt insisted on buying a brand of health care products, not to buy, they kept calling crying. In the end, I had to go to six pharmacies to get what she wanted.

The work is small and tiring. But I guess it's called doing your job.
